<h2 style="padding-top:30px;">Looks cool, but how the hell do I use it?</h2>

<p>Picture.ly is a 'Visual Discovery Engine'. Sounds fancy, right? In actuality, Picture.ly is just searching popular social networks for recent and public images based on keywords or hashtags. So you could search for anything like <%= link_to("coffee", search_path(:q=>"coffee")) %> or <%= link_to("beach", search_path(:q=>"beach")) %>. Yea, pretty cool. Below are some of our favorite uses of Picture.ly</p>

<h3>Cool Tips</h3>
<ul>
	<li> Want to see recent news events? Use Picture.ly! In 2011, Picture.ly was able to capture the <%= link_to("#occupywallstreet", search_path(:q=>"occupywallstreet")) %> through user photos</li>
	<li>Hosting an event? Use Picture.ly! Ask guests to take pictures with a hashtag and upload to twitter. Use the Picture.ly to view all your pictures from the event by searching for your event's hashtag'</li>
	<li>Looking for travel inspiration? Search Picture.ly for your favorite city. Check out <%= link_to("Paris", search_path(:q=>"paris")) %></li>
	<li>Create a picture magazine using the Picture.ly RSS Feed and Flipboard or (your favorite RSS reader). Just enter the search rss feed url into your reader.</li>
	
</ul>
<h3>Picture.ly Shortcuts</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Search for a keyword using http://picture.ly/keyword/{keyword} example: <%= link_to("http://picture.ly/keyword/beach","http://picture.ly/keyword/beach")%></li>
	<li>Search for city using http://picture.ly/city/{city name} example: <%= link_to("http://picture.ly/city/san+francisco","http://picture.ly/city/san+francisco")%></li>
	<li>Search for photos shared by twitter user using http://picture.ly/twittername/{twittername} example: <%= link_to("http://picture.ly/twiteruser/picturely","http://picture.ly/twitteruser/picturely")%></li>
</ul>
