<p><h5>Frequently Asked Questions</h5></p>
<p>Q: I uploaded pictures to Twitter last month. I can't find them on the site.</br>
A: Picture.ly currently only displays recent photos. Which means you will only see photos uploaded to twitter within the last 4 to 6 days. In addition, our photo services are limited to Instagram, YFrog, Twitpic, Twimg, and Lockerz. We are working to include more photo hosts.</p>
<p>Q: What other social networks can I search using Picture.ly?</br>
	A: Currently, Picture.ly is only searching Twitter for alpha product. However, we plan to expand to more social networks.</p>
<p>Q: Why is your FAQ so short? </br>
	A: We're pretty new here. So, if you have any questions, email us, and we will post frequent questions to the site.</p>
